// Diagram from Code Generator
// Parses TypeScript/JavaScript source files using regex to generate three types of
// Mermaid diagrams: class hierarchies, import dependency graphs, and module maps.

FUNCTION readFiles(filePaths) -> FileContent[]
  Attempt to read each file at the provided paths. Skip unreadable files silently.
  Return array of { path, content } for all successfully read files.

---

FUNCTION extractClasses(files) -> ClassInfo[]
  Scan each file's content for class and interface declarations using regex.
  For each match, extract: name, extends parent, implements list.
  Find the class body by locating the opening brace and tracking depth.
  Within the body, extract method signatures (up to 10) and property declarations (up to 10).
  Skip false positives in method/property patterns (control flow keywords).
  Return list of ClassInfo objects.

---

FUNCTION generateClassDiagram(files) -> string
  CALLS: extractClasses (diagram-codegen)
  Extract all class info from files. IF none found, return a placeholder diagram.
  Build classDiagram Mermaid syntax: emit each class with its properties and methods,
  then emit inheritance (--|>) and implementation (..|>) relationships.

---

FUNCTION extractImports(files, projectRoot) -> ImportInfo[]
  Scan each file for import statements. Only include relative imports (starting with ".").
  Resolve relative import paths to project-root-relative paths.
  Return list of { from, to } import relationships.

---

FUNCTION sanitizeMermaidId(str) -> string
  Replace non-alphanumeric characters with underscores, strip leading/trailing underscores.
  Prefix digit-leading IDs with "f". Return a fallback random ID for empty strings.

---

FUNCTION generateDependencyDiagram(files, projectRoot) -> string
  CALLS: extractImports (diagram-codegen)
  Extract all import relationships. IF none, return a placeholder.
  Emit graph LR with node definitions using basenames as labels,
  then edges for each import relationship.

---

FUNCTION generateModuleDiagram(files, projectRoot) -> string
  CALLS: extractImports (diagram-codegen)
  Group files by their directory. Build graph TD with one subgraph per directory.
  Add edges only for cross-directory imports (intra-directory imports are omitted).

---

FUNCTION handleDiagramFromCode(project, filePaths, diagramType) -> { mermaidSource }  EXPORT
  CALLS: readFiles (diagram-codegen), generateClassDiagram (diagram-codegen), generateDependencyDiagram (diagram-codegen), generateModuleDiagram (diagram-codegen)
  Read all provided files. Throw if none could be read.
  Dispatch to the appropriate diagram generator based on diagramType (class, dependency, module).
  Return { success: true, mermaidSource }.
